{"copyright": {"licenseType": "NO", "determinationType": "OTHER", "thirdPartyContentCondition": "NOT_SET"}, "subjectCategories": ["ASTROPHYSICS"], "exportControl": {"isExportControl": "NO", "ear": "NO", "itar": "NO"}, "distributionDate": "2019-07-11T00:00:00.0000000+00:00", "fundingNumbers": [{"number": "W-7405-ENG-48", "type": "CONTRACT_GRANT"}, {"number": "NAS5-27670", "type": "CONTRACT_GRANT"}], "title": "Needling the early universe", "stiType": "REPRINT", "distribution": "PUBLIC", "submittedDate": "2013-08-13T14:43:00.0000000+00:00", "authorAffiliations": [{"sequence": 0, "submissionId": 19880036578, "meta": {"author": {"name": "Hawkins, Isabel"}, "organization": {"name": "Lawrence Livermore National Laboratory", "location": "Livermore, CA, United States"}}, "id": "fa98558a7fd24aa897cf98310ef17bdc"}, {"sequence": 1, "submissionId": 19880036578, "meta": {"author": {"name": "Wright, Edward L."}, "organization": {"name": "California, University", "location": "Los Angeles, United States"}}, "id": "df9961b6ce0a484a9f8a39f2995695c5"}], "stiTypeDetails": "Reprint (Version printed in journal)", "technicalReviewType": "TECHNICAL_REVIEW_TYPE_NONE", "modified": "2011-08-18T00:00:00.0000000+00:00", "id": 19880036578, "sourceIdentifiers": [{"number": "doi:10.1086/165879", "type": "DOI"}], "created": "2013-08-13T14:43:00.0000000+00:00", "center": {"code": "CDMS", "name": "Legacy CDMS", "id": "092d6e0881874968859b972d39a888dc"}, "onlyAbstract": false, "sensitiveInformation": 2, "abstract": "The possibility that the whole microwave background can be produced by a bright population of pregalactic stars at a redshift of a few hundred is explored. The radiation is thermalized by a combination of amorphous silicate, amorphous carbon, graphite, and needle-shaped conducting grains which give rise to the opacity needed at wavelengths greater than 3 cm. The occurrence of distortion in a primordial microwave background spectrum due to its interaction with Population III stars and dust i